Musa CAD — license
==================

Musa CAD is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License, version 3,
or (at your option) any later version (LGPL-3.0-or-later).

SPDX-License-Identifier: LGPL-3.0-or-later
Copyright (C) 2026 Kiran Pranay

The full license texts are in this repository:
  - COPYING          — the GNU General Public License v3 (GPL-3.0)
  - COPYING.LESSER   — the GNU Lesser General Public License v3 (LGPL-3.0)
LGPL-3 is written as a set of additional permissions on top of GPL-3, so both
texts are included.

What this means, in plain terms (not legal advice):
  - You may use Musa CAD, including by dynamically linking it into your own
    software — including closed-source/proprietary software — provided you
    preserve the user's ability to replace the Musa CAD component with a
    modified version (the LGPL "relink" requirement) and you keep these license
    notices.
  - If you modify Musa CAD itself and distribute those modifications, the
    modified Musa CAD source must be made available under the LGPL-3.
  - Musa CAD links Qt6 dynamically (Qt is itself LGPL-3). DWG import/export is
    performed by an EXTERNAL converter invoked as a separate process; no DWG
    library is linked into or shipped with Musa CAD. See
    docs/THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md.

This file is a summary; the COPYING / COPYING.LESSER texts are authoritative.
